REGARDING RABBITMQ:
IMP: run email service first then core(yet to figure out the rreson for solving this issue)
Fix for the PRECONDITION_FAILED
Right now the error still means: one declaration of profile-activation-queue has x-dead-letter-exchange='', and another declaration has no x-dead-letter-exchange at all.
To eliminate this completely, I’ve changed the setup so that:
Only email-service (the consumer) declares the queue and DLQ.
core-service (the publisher) no longer declares any queues at all – it just uses RabbitTemplate to send to the queue by name.


